  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was designed to investigate the analgesic effect of bilateral superficial cervical
      plexus block in patients undergoing robot-assisted endoscopic thyroidectomy. The
      investigators hypothesized that bilateral superficial cervical plexus blockade would reduce
      the patient's pain score by more than 10 (on a VAS scale of 0~100) compared to a placebo
      group and control group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
